<br />I actually did program once in some assembly for the x86 in a class in college 10 years ago but it was only one semester and programming was only part of the class. It was basically a class on understanding microprocessor architecture and we spent most of the time on the hardware side. So basically I understand the concept but even my teacher said that most people who program in assembly end up in the loony bin.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> 
